    "analysis": "We inspected metric anomalies for ts-order-service and found a clear latency-90 spike at 2024-01-22 10:59:00+00:00 (max ≈ 0.382s) plus other anomalous KPI spikes later in the window. Earlier trace-level attempts to find calls directed to the candidate services using a 'to_ts-<candidate>' pattern returned no rows, likely due to trace naming differences. We also have a labeled trace-window table that includes many trace.* groups for the candidate services (e.g., trace.from_root.row_count, trace.from_ts-..., trace.to_ts-... for some services). According to the localization rules, we must identify the most downstream faulty service among the candidate set by inspecting trace naming patterns (which indicate caller->callee relationships) and trace anomalies. To do that reliably we first need to list the available trace_name patterns for each candidate in the incident window so we can correctly identify which trace metrics represent incoming calls to a candidate (callee) vs outgoing calls (caller). This will let us locate which candidate appears as a downstream target in anomalous traces and therefore is likeliest the root cause.",
