}

{
    "analysis": "Last step attempted to find traces from the global 'root' to any of the five candidate services but returned an empty set. Summary of what we have so far: global thresholds for metrics/traces were computed; metric anomalies were labeled in-window; candidates ts-order-service and ts-travel-service show the strongest metric signals (ts-order-service has an early latency-90 spike at 2024-01-22 10:59:00+00:00). Trace-based caller->callee resolution toward the candidate services did not yield direct root->candidate rows (empty), so traces did not clearly identify which candidate is the downstream faulty service. According to the diagnosis workflow, when traces are ambiguous we should use logs to refine the failure reason and to corroborate which candidate experienced a real sustained fault rather than isolated metric spikes. Therefore the next step is to compute global thresholds for log groups and inspect logs for the five candidate services within the incident window to detect log anomalies and earliest timestamps.",
